events.description:
Next Extended Brings together developer communities around the world to take part in the Next’18 experience, either during the conference or even after!
These events run from late July to October. Next Extended allows local developers to access exciting Next’18 content and engage with community through local speakers. activities and hands-on-labs.

events.name: #IndiaBuildsActions Build Actions on Google for Odisha (Invite Only)
events.description:
Actions on Google and Google Assistant are one of the major Google technical areas and we want to invite the whole developer community to learn about creating Actions for the Google Assistant.
“#IndiaBuildsActions” is an open and modular event series designed for individuals and communities in India to build actions that #SolveForIndia.
Join us to build innovative and unique actions that are locally relevant, taking into account aspects of language, devices, battery consumption and connectivity, solving problems for India in the space of agriculture, education, healthcare, fintech, e-commerce etc.

events.name: Asynchronous Application Design using Cloud PubSub
events.description: The session in this meetup will cover the basic features of Cloud Pub Sub and illustrate through an example nodejs application about how this the power of Pub Sub can be used to design asynchronous application architecture.

events.name: Design Sprint - Create Great Products
events.description:
Event Date: 13 January, Sunday
Timing: 9:30 am to 1:30 pm
Venue: KIIT TBI, Patia, Bhubaneshwar

How to attend this event?
Step 1. Fill this form to register: https://goo.gl/forms/6AijkxSaFthqnh5y1
Step 2: Join the waitlist here: https://www.meetup.com/GDG-Bhubaneswar/events/257677207/
Step 3: Go through all the FAQs of the event mentioned below.

What is the design sprint?
A design sprint is a time-constrained, five-phase process that uses design thinking with the aim of reducing the risk when bringing a new product, service or a feature to the market.
In simple words, it is turning your idea into a prototype for building a new product.

What's the agenda?
Your team will be given a problem statement to solve. Your team needs to finish the task. The best team wins.

What will be the problem statement to solve?
You will be given the problem statement on the event day.

Am I eligible for the Design Sprint?
If you are one of the following, then you are fit for the event.
1) Developers and product owners
2) UX/UI Designers

Note: If you are a student and creative enough to turn your idea into a product, decide it's flow, mockups, and prototype then this event is for you too.

Why be a part of this?
- Design Sprint will help you define and mount viable product with a validation plan in the markets.
- Good opportunity to turn ideas to product

Is it teamwork? How can I form a team?
Yes, it is. You can come to the event and form the team.

What's the takeaway?
Win exciting Google goodies and great learning experience.

Note: Registration closes as we reach 90 registrations.

Seats are limited. See you at the event!

events.name: Google Cloud Study Jam
events.description:
India is one of the largest and fastest growing cloud services market in Asia Pacific. According to Gartner, India’s IT spending is projected to total $89.2 billion in 2019. The IT buying pattern in India signals the increased use of cloud services by organizations.” This has led to an increase in demand to learn about Google Cloud, Machine Learning and Kubernetes.
To cater to this growing demand, in May 2018, we welcomed our first Google Cloud Developer Community (GCDC) in India, and now we are 11 communities strong - Ahmedabad, Bangalore, Bhubaneswar, Chennai, Coimbatore, Hyderabad, Indore, Kolkata, Mumbai, New Delhi, and Pune with more than 10000 members. These communities host frequent meetups to discuss topics like Kubernetes, Google App Engine, Data Science, Machine Learning on Google Cloud. These communities are growing rapidly in terms of membership and frequency of technical meet-ups.
To provide developers an opportunity to stay ahead of the curve, we are happy to introduce Cloud Study Jams in India. Study Jams are community-run study groups for developers. This is a great opportunity to bring members of the community together to learn something in person. These trainings give developers a specific skill they can use for personal development or career advancement.
